---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import BrandMark from '../components/BrandMark.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---
<BaseLayout>
  <Header>
    <BrandMark slot="mark" />
  </Header>

  <main>
    <section class="section hero-section">
      <div class="shell surface-dark pad hero-card">
        <div class="hero-copy">
          <div class="meta-label">Trust</div>
          <h1>Trust should be explicit system structure.</h1>
          <p>
            Aster frames trust as rooted authority, admission policy, delegated capability,
            and routine rotation. It should feel legible to operators rather than hidden inside infrastructure folklore.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="trust-rail">
          <span>Root</span>
          <span>Admission</span>
          <span>Capability</span>
          <span>Rotation</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="shell surface-light-wrap">
        <div class="surface-light pad">
          <div class="section-head">
            <div>
              <div class="meta-label">Trust model</div>
              <h2>Portable trust, operator-shaped.</h2>
            </div>
            <p>
              The point is not vague security language. The point is to make authority,
              membership, and delegated action concrete enough to reason about and operate.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="grid grid-2">
            <article class="card light-card">
              <div class="meta-label">Root authority</div>
              <h3>Highest trust anchor</h3>
              <p>An offline or carefully controlled root defines the top of the trust tree rather than outsourcing authority to ambient infrastructure.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="card light-card">
              <div class="meta-label">Admission</div>
              <h3>Explicit membership</h3>
              <p>Producers and peers are admitted according to policy, making trust boundaries visible and reviewable.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="card light-card">
              <div class="meta-label">Capability issuance</div>
              <h3>Delegation over blanket access</h3>
              <p>Rights can be granted with scope and intent instead of assuming every authenticated peer should do everything.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="card light-card">
              <div class="meta-label">Rotation and revocation</div>
              <h3>Normal operational behavior</h3>
              <p>Keys, leases, and authority can change without collapsing service identity or contract continuity.</p>
            </article>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="shell surface-dark pad">
        <div class="section-head dark">
          <div>
            <div class="meta-label">Positioning</div>
            <h2>Serious, calm, and legible.</h2>
          </div>
          <p>
            This page should communicate that Aster is not using decentralisation as a vibe.
            Trust is presented as an auditable model for identity-first systems operating across mixed environments.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .pad { padding: 26px; }
  .hero-section { padding-top: 24px; }
  .hero-card, .section-head { display: grid; gap: 18px; }
  .hero-card { grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.25fr) 240px; align-items: end; }
  .hero-copy h1, .section-head h2 { margin: 0; letter-spacing: -0.05em; }
  .hero-copy h1 { font-size: clamp(40px, 6vw, 72px); line-height: 0.98; color: var(--cloud-strong); max-width: 11ch; }
  .hero-copy p, .section-head p { margin: 0; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.6; max-width: 64ch; }
  .hero-copy p { color: var(--mist); }
  .section-head { grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.1fr) minmax(280px, 0.9fr); margin-bottom: 22px; align-items: end; }
  .section-head h2 { font-size: clamp(30px, 4vw, 48px); line-height: 1.02; color: var(--ink); }
  .section-head p { color: var(--ink-soft); }
  .section-head.dark h2 { color: var(--cloud-strong); }
  .section-head.dark p { color: var(--mist); }
  .trust-rail { display: grid; gap: 10px; }
  .trust-rail span { border-radius: 999px; padding: 10px 12px; border: 1px solid rgba(230,192,107,0.22); background: rgba(230,192,107,0.08); color: var(--cloud-strong); font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: .08em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .grid { display: grid; gap: 16px; }
  .grid-2 { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr)); }
  .card { border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: 18px; }
  .light-card { border: 1px solid rgba(25, 37, 51, 0.1); background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.72); }
  .meta-label { margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 11px; line-height: 1.2; letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .card h3 { margin: 0; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.15; letter-spacing: -0.025em; color: var(--ink); }
  .card p { margin: 8px 0 0; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5; color: var(--ink-soft); }
  @media (max-width: 960px) {
    .hero-card, .section-head, .grid-2 { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .pad { padding: 22px; }
  }
</style>
